            <h2>Island Garden City of Samal</h2>
            <h3>The Urban Center in a Garden Setting</h3>
            <hr>
            <img src="<?= $this->webroot ?>theme/weatherph/img/tourism/islandGardenCityOfSamal1.png" alt="">

            <p>An enchanting paradise - an island, a garden, and a city. Located at the heart of Davao Gulf of southern Philippines, the Island Garden City of Samal (IGACOS) teems with rich flora and fauna bedecked in captivating waterfalls, challenging ridges, fascinating cave systems, and picturesque underwater gardens.</p>
            <p>With all these ingredients combined, Samal has unsurprisingly emerged as ‘Regional Hub for Recreation and Amity in Southern Philippines’, a haven for wellness tourism, outdoor adventure, aquasports, cultural and eco-tourism - a rare destination with almost has it all.</p>
            <p>No wonder that the Island has become a favorite gateway of all types of tourists - a hidden nook for discriminating jetsetters, a refuge for nature trippers, a preferred lair for family excursionists, and as a playground for outdoor adventurists wanting to burn their adrenalins.</p>
            <p>The City is an Island, a cluster of nine islands at the heart of Davao Gulf with scenic seacaspes pristine coastlines, and turquoise marine waters, a 118-kilometer of fine, white, sandy coastlines, home to more than 50 commercial resorts and hundreds of private getaways.</p>
            <p>The City is a Garden. Laidback urban landscape in a garden set- ting, numerous scenic natural parks and open spaces, balanced ecosystems (intact natural endowment), more pedestrians, bicycle and tree lanes, and green oriented neigborhoods.</p>
            <p>IGACOS is an urbanizing community of dignified constituents, equipped with good urban amenities living in an atmosphere of good governance.</p>

