            <h3>IGACOS’ Must Do List</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>1. Close encounters with millions of fruit bats at the Monfort Bat Sanctuary and Conservation Park. Declared in 2009 by Guinness World Record as home of the world’s biggest colony of Geoffrey’s Rousette Fruit Bats numbering approximate- ly 1.8-2.5 million as validated by the Bats Conservation International.</li>
                <li>2. Cliff hanging at Bito Depression and Plunging at the Hagimat Falls. Burn adrenalin in rappelling 273-feet natural limestone walls, then commune with nature as you go in a picnic beneath the shadow of coconut grooves, or spread your tents in the midst of lush vegetation.</li>
                <li>3. Island cruise and bask in any of our numerous resorts. Cruise around the island and lay idle at the numerous commercial resorts and private getaways along the 118-kilometer stretch of coastlines.</li>
                <li>4. Scuba diving. Diving into the depths of Talikud or in Liguid Islands and many other dive spots will reveal dazzling coral gardens and colorful underwater vistas with jaw dropping tropical marine life.</li>
                <li>5. Celebrate during festivals. Celebrate with Samalenos on their founding anniversary every March 07. The weeklong festivity highlights sand sculputure competition (Pag-Ukit sa Pantad), fluvial parade of colorful boats (Bigiw Regatta), banca race (bangkarera). The merry making is accentuated with the colorful stitlts (karang) and Mascot Competition.</li>
            </ol>
            <h3>Major destinations and cultural activities</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>1. IGACOS Festival - This week-long festivity in celebration of the founding anniversary of the City starts on March 1 and culminates on March 07.</li>
                <li>2. KABASAN Festival. “Kabasan” (literally means seashells) celebrates the rich and colorful ‘bounties of the seas’ culminating on May 28, the founding anniversary of the old municipality of Babak. The festival showcases ala Mardigras street-dancing, street parties, and concerts, bikini open, fireworks, among others.</li>
                <li>3. White Nights Festival - Owing to its moniker to the white sandy beachline of celebration venue which is Kaputian (white) Poblacion, the event is a festival of history, culture and arts in commemoration of the founding anniversary of the old municipality of Kaputian.</li>
            </ol>

